OL,3,CBournemouth stroke patient campaigns
OL,4,Cfor better rehabilitation for others
OL,6,FA man from Dorset who suffered a
OL,7,Fstroke is backing calls for more
OL,8,Finvestment in vital rehabilitation
OL,9,Fafter a new survey reveals that most
OL,10,Fregions are seriously underfunded and
OL,11,Funderstaffed.
OL,13,FDavid Stadelman, 73, who lives in
OL,14,FHighcliffe near Bournemouth, had a
OL,15,Fstroke two years ago.
OL,17,FHe credits the excellent care he
OL,18,Freceived and ongoing therapy for his
OL,19,Fgood recovery, but he wants every
OL,20,Fpatient to have that same benefit.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/4
