OL,3,CBournemouth stroke patient campaigns
OL,4,Cfor better rehabilitation for others
OL,6,FThe Chartered Society of Physiotherapy
OL,7,Fclaims that community stroke services
OL,8,Fhave on average 26% fewer
OL,9,Fphysiotherapists than recommended, and
OL,10,FAcute Stroke teams are down by 15%
OL,11,Fwhich is leaving some people with
OL,12,Favoidable disabilities.
OL,14,FThe government says it accepts it is
OL,15,Ffailing many patients, but is
OL,16,Fcommitted to reducing the number of
OL,17,Fpeople who die from heart disease and
OL,18,Fstrokes by a quarter over the next ten
OL,19,Fyears.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
